The paper deals with human pose estimation in an operating room using RGB-D data. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image processing and analysis. The use of this technology in an operating room also makes it relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also proposes a novel descriptor for depth images, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
